Exercise 1: Setting Up JUnit (Basic Testing)

Description:
This exercise demonstrates how to set up and run a basic unit test using JUnit 5. It involves creating a simple Java method (e.g., add two numbers) and writing a test case to validate its output.

Expected Input (in test method):
add(3, 7)

Expected Output (from test result):
Test passed: 3 + 7 = 10
